<h1>JavaScript Tutorial</h1>
<p>JavaScript is a popular and globally used language, extensively used in web development. It's simple to grasp, and this tutorial aims to help you learn from the basics to advanced topics.</p>
<h2>Interactive Examples in Each Chapter</h2>
<p>Our interactive code editor allows you to try modifying the provided examples and see the result instantly. This way, you get to learn by doing!</p>
<h4>Example: Introduction to JS</h4>
<button onclick="alert('Current Date and Time: '+ new Date())">Click me!</button>
<p>Tutorial sections can be navigated through the menu. For larger displays, the menu is persistently on the left; for smaller ones, click the top menu icon to display it.</p>
<h2>Learn by Examples</h2>
<p>Examples offer easier-to-understand learning material than lengthy texts. Alongside textual explanations, we provide "Try it Yourself" examples to clarify concepts. Make sure to try them out to understand better and learn faster!</p>
<h3>Why Learn JavaScript?</h3>
<p>All web developers should learn three languages: HTML for defining webpage content, CSS for designing webpage layout, and JavaScript for programming webpage behavior. This tutorial covers all versions of JavaScript.</p>
<h3>Adaptable Learning Pace</h3>
<p>This tutorial allows you to learn at a comfortable pace. If certain parts seem challenging, feel free to revisit them until they're clear. Practice and coding constantly are the keys to becoming a proficient programmer!</p>
